casebody.data:
THE STERN HOLDING COMPANY, PLAINTIFF-APPELLANT, v. PHILIP O’CONNOR, THOMAS O’CONNOR AND JAMES O’CONNOR, CO-PARTNERS TRADING AS O’CONNOR BROS., DEFENDANTS-RESPONDENTS. Submitted October term, 1937 Decided January 28, 1938.

Before Justices Lloyd, Case and Donges.

Eor the appellant, Schumann & Schumann. Eor the respondents, Nicholas S. Schloeder. Per Curiam.

Eor the reasons expressed in the case of Stem Holding Co. v. O’Connor, 119 N. J. L. 291, the judgment in this case is reversed.
